              "name": "RoadmapIds",
              "value": "513432"
            },
            {
              "name": "Summary",
              "value": "A new Copilot button will appear in the bottom-right corner of the OneDrive and SharePoint file previewer, replacing the command bar button. It provides access to Copilot chat and contextual prompts for paid Copilot license users. Rollout begins mid-November 2025, excluding GCC, GCCH, and DoD customers."
            },
            {
              "name": "Platforms",
              "value": "Web"
            }
          ],
          "body": {
            "contentType": "html",
            "content": "<p>Updated December 12, 2025: We have updated the timeline. We will not be rolling out this feature to GCC, GCCH and DoD customers at this time. We apologize for the inconvenience.&nbsp;</p><p><b>[Introduction]</b></p><p></p><p>We've added a new <i>Copilot button</i> that gives users a quick and visible entry point to Copilot directly within the <i>file previewer</i> in OneDrive and SharePoint. This button appears near the bottom-right corner of the file previewer (instead of in the <i>command bar</i>) and surfaces contextual prompts for Copilot-supported file types. It also provides access to the <i>Copilot chat</i>. This feature will be available to users with a paid Copilot license</p><p>This message is associated with Roadmap ID <a href=\"https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?filters=&amp;searchterms=513432\" target=\"_blank\">513432</a>.</p><p><b>[When this will happen:]</b></p><p>General Availability (Worldwide): We will begin rolling out mid-November 2025 and expect to complete by end of February 2026 (previously December 2025).</p>\n<p><b>[How this affects your organization:]</b></p>\n<p><b>Who is affected:</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Users who preview files in OneDrive or SharePoint.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>What will happen:</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A new<i> Copilot button</i> will appear in the bottom-right corner of the file previewer.</li><img src=\"https://cxcs.microsoft.net/file/ccp/en-us/ead76838-1d4d-48b8-ac20-09ce4c56d9ce\" style=\"width: 400px;\" alt=\"user settings\">\n<li>This button provides access to <i>Copilot chat</i> and contextual prompts based on the file type.</li>\n<li>The previous <i>Copilot command</i> in the <i>command bar</i> will be removed.</li>\n<li>No changes to admin policies or settings are required.</li>\n<li>This feature is enabled for <b>users with the paid Copilot license add-on</b>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>[What you can do to prepare:]</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>No action is required at this time.</li>\n<li>Communicate this change to helpdesk or support staff.</li>\n<li>Update internal documentation to reflect the new location of the <i>Copilot button</i>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>[Compliance considerations:]</b></p>\n<p>No compliance considerations identified, review as appropriate for your organization.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "startDateTime": "2025-09-02T23:17:18Z",
          "endDateTime": "2026-03-02T08:00:00Z",
          "lastModifiedDateTime": "2025-12-12T22:21:31.15Z",
          "title": "(Updated) Microsoft Copilot dashboard (in Viva Insights): New benchmarks to compare Copilot usage across organizations",
          "id": "MC1146816",
          "category": "stayInformed",
          "severity": "normal",
          "tags": [
            "Updated message",
            "New feature",
            "User impact",
            "Admin impact"
          ],
          "isMajorChange": false,
          "actionRequiredByDateTime": null,
          "services": [
            "Microsoft Viva",
            "Microsoft Copilot (Microsoft 365)"
          ],
          "hasAttachments": false,
          "details": [
            {
              "name": "RoadmapIds",
              "value": "495464"
            },
            {
              "name": "Summary",
              "value": "Microsoft is adding benchmarks to the Copilot dashboard in Viva Insights, enabling organizations to compare internal and external Copilot usage. Rollout begins mid-October 2025. Benchmarks use anonymized data, include admin controls, and help improve adoption strategies. Organizations should review access and update training accordingly."
            },
            {
              "name": "Platforms",
              "value": "Web"
            }
          ],
          "body": {
            "contentType": "html",
            "content": "<p>Updated December 12, 2025: We have updated the timeline. Thank you for your patience.</p><p>Weâ€™re introducing <b>Benchmarks</b> in the <i>Microsoft Copilot dashboard (in Viva Insights)</i>. This new feature enables organizations to compare Copilot usage internally across cohorts and externally against similar companies. These insights help identify adoption trends and opportunities to improve Copilot engagement.</p>\n\n<p>This message is associated with Microsoft 365 Roadmap ID: <a href=\"https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?filters=&amp;searchterms=495464\" target=\"_blank\">495464</a><b>.</b></p>\n\n<b>When this will happen</b>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Targeted Release (Worldwide):</b>&nbsp;We will begin rolling out in mid-October 2025 (previously late September) and expect to complete by late October 2025 (previously early October).</li>\n<li><b>General Availability (Worldwide):</b>&nbsp;We will begin rolling out in late October 2025 (previously mid-October) and expect to complete by end of January 2026 (previously late November 2025).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<b>How this affects your organization</b>\n<p>Once available, the Copilot dashboard will include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>External benchmarks</b> to compare your percentage of active Copilot users with:\n  <ulights web app - Viva Insights | Microsoft Viva | Microsoft Learn</a></li></ul><ul>\n</ul>\n\n<b>Compliance considerations</b>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody><tr><th>Question</th><th>Answer</th></tr>\n<tr><td>Does the change store new customer data?</td><td>Yes. Benchmark data includes anonymized usage metrics that are stored within Microsoft 365 services.</td></tr>\n\n\n<tr><td>Does the change include an admin control and can it be controlled through Entra ID group membership?</td><td>Yes. Access to the Copilot dashboard can be disabled using Viva Feature Access Management controls and can be managed using Entra ID group membership.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>"
          },
